description: Date and time format.
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

All timestamps must use the following format:

yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss.SSS±HH

Separator: Use a space (' ') between date and time.

Precision: Use milliseconds (3 digits after the decimal point).

Timezone: Include numeric UTC offset in the format ±HH, e.g., +00 or +02.

Timezone precision: Offset must include at least hours, but may optionally include ±HH:mm if needed.